    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "DENVER. March THE long\nillness of John H. Murphy. veteran\nlegal adviser for the Western Fed\nGrafton of Labor, ended last night\nin death at his home in this city.\nHe was 46 years of age.\n\n\nMurphy laid the foundations of\nthe defense OF the Meyer. Haywood\nand Pettibone cases. He was so\nweak that it was feared he would\ndie If taken TO Idaho for the trials.\nbut he made the trip there and back\nfrequently at the point OF death. In\naddition to being counsel for the\nfederation he was editor of the\nMiners Magazine and attorney for\nthe locomotive firemen."
    }
  ]
